1)  Download Clang+LLVM 3.3 binaries from here
        http://llvm.org/releases/download.html#3.3
        http://llvm.org/releases/3.3/clang+llvm-3.3-Ubuntu-13.04-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.bz2

1b) Unpack and add them to PATH.
        Adding them to path isn't strictly necessary, but since using KLEE
        necessitates using Clang as IR compiler, it will save some time.

2)  Download and build Clang+LLVM3.3 from here
        http://llvm.org/releases/download.html#3.3
        http://llvm.org/releases/3.3/llvm-3.3.src.tar.gz
        http://llvm.org/releases/3.3/clang-3.3.src.tar.gz
            note that clang sources go into llvm/tools/clang directory
        http://llvm.org/releases/3.3/compiler-rt-3.3.src.tar.gz

        ./configure --enable-optimized --enable-assertions

3)  Download and build STP (in submodules)
        cmake -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=OFF -DENABLE_PYTHON_INTERFACE:BOOL=OFF
        make

<This project doesn't use uclibc and POSIX, so they are skipped.>

4)  Download and build KLEE (in submodules)
        ./configure --with-stp=<full/path/to/stp> \
        --with-llvm=<full/path/to/llvm> \
        make DISABLE_ASSERTIONS=0 ENABLE_OPTIMIZED=1 ENABLE_SHARED=0

4b) Optionally run KLEE test suite
        make check
        make unittests
